The paper proposes a data-driven approach for financial time-series forecasting using a neural architecture composed of Generalized Operational Perceptron. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also deals with imbalanced data distribution, which is a common problem in financial data analysis, indicating that it could belong to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category. The use of neural networks and deep learning techniques in financial time-series forecasting also suggests that the paper could belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel algorithm for neural architecture learning, which could make it relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
